{"lemma":"أَبْكَمَ","slug":"أَبْكَمَ","root":"ب.ك.م","root_slug":"ب-ك-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ك-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَبْكَم","root":"بكم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3091"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"mute"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root ب ك م (b k m)."},"ipa":["/ʔab.kam/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3091","headword_ar":"اَبْكَمٌ","root":"bkm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakiymN","text_ar":"بَكِيمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axorasu","text_ar":"اَخْرَسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dumb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by natural conformation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from inability to find words to express what he would say"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not having understanding to reply,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor ability to frame speech well,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"though possessing the faculty of speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whereas"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Axrs","text_ar":"اخرس"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies speechless, or destitute of the faculty of speech, by natural conformation, (T, Msb, TA,) like the beast that lacks the faculty of articulation; (T, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unable to find words to express what he would say; unable to reply:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dumb by natural conformation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakomaA='u","text_ar":"بَكْمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bukomN","text_ar":"بُكْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bukomaAnN","text_ar":"بُكْمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) both pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abokamu","text_ar":"اَبْكَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sum~N","text_ar":"صُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sum~aAnN","text_ar":"صُمَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSam~u","text_ar":"اَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakiymN","text_ar":"بَكِيمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abokaAmN","text_ar":"اَبْكَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) In the Kur ii. 166,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bukomN","text_ar":"بُكْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means persons"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the condition of him who has been born dumb:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deprived of their intellects:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ignorant and ignoble;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because not profiting much by the faculty"},{"kind":"page_break","n":242},{"kind":"text","text":"of speech, so that they are as though they had been deprived of it. (IAth, TA.) The phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonapN Sam~aA='u bakomaA='u EamoyaA='u","text_ar":"فِتْنَةٌ صَمَّا=ءُ بَكْمَا=ءُ عَمْيَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., [lit.] meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sedition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the like,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deaf, dumb, blind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"applies to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ftnp","text_ar":"فتنة"},{"kind":"text","text":"that does not withdraw, or become removed: or, as some say, to one which, by reason of the confusion attending it, and the perishing of the sound and the sick therein, is likened to the deaf and dumb and blind who does not pursue the right course to a thing, but goes at random like the weak-sighted she-camel. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Msb","IAar","T","TA","AZ","IAth","Zj"]}]}}